overview: The user initiated a review of their recently implemented sleep
  questionnaire application, seeking to confirm adherence to acceptance criteria
  and identify any missing functionalities. The agent conducted a comprehensive
  analysis, pinpointing several key areas for improvement. Subsequently, the
  agent proceeded to implement these enhancements. This included integrating a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference, complete with critical safety
  warnings for high scores. The agent also added sophisticated detection logic
  for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome, providing tailored recommendations for each. Finally, a dedicated
  resources section with placeholder outbound links to professional sleep and
  mental health directories was incorporated into both the interactive report
  and the PDF download, significantly enriching the application's utility for
  users seeking further guidance.
